SIMPLE: matronize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Matronize
<hw>Mat"ron*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Matronized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Matronizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To make a matron of; to make matronlike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Childbed <qex>matronizes</qex> the giddiest spirits.</q>
<rj><qau>Richardson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To act the part of a matron toward; to superintend;
to chaperone; <as>as, to <ex>matronize</ex> an assembly</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Matronlike</ent>⟦br⟧
